<h1>Cookie Policy</h1>

<p>Effective Date: [@ViewBag.Date]</p>

<p>This Cookie Policy ("Policy") explains how cookies and similar tracking technologies are used when you visit or interact with our website ("Website"). This Policy should be read alongside our Privacy Policy, which provides more information about how we collect, use, and disclose your personal data.</p>

<h2>What are Cookies?</h2>

<p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently, enhance user experience, and provide information to website owners.</p>

<h2>How We Use Cookies</h2>

<p>We use cookies and similar technologies for various purposes, including:</p>

<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> These cookies are necessary for the proper functioning of the Website. They enable you to navigate our site and use its features. Without these cookies, certain services and functionalities may be unavailable.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> We use analytics cookies to collect information about how visitors use our Website, such as the pages they visit, the time spent on each page, and any error messages encountered. This data helps us analyze and improve the performance and usability of our Website.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Advertising Cookies:</strong> We may use advertising cookies to deliver targeted advertisements that are relevant to your interests. These cookies collect information about your browsing habits and enable us to display personalized content and ads.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Functionality Cookies:</strong> Functionality cookies allow the Website to remember choices you make (such as your preferred language or region) and provide enhanced features. These cookies can also be used to remember changes you have made to text size, font, and other customizable elements of web pages.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Social Media Cookies:</strong> Our Website may include social media features or plugins that allow you to connect with your social networks and share content. These features may use cookies to track your browsing activity across different websites. Please refer to the respective social media platform's privacy policy for more information on their cookie usage.
    </li>
</ol>

<h2>Your Cookie Choices</h2>

<p>When you visit our Website for the first time, we will ask for your consent to use cookies, except for essential cookies, which are necessary for the functioning of the Website. You can manage your cookie preferences by adjusting the settings in your web browser or through the cookie consent banner displayed on our Website.</p>

<p>Please note that blocking or disabling certain types of cookies may impact the functionality of our Website and limit your ability to fully experience its features.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>

<p>We may also allow third parties, such as advertising networks and service providers, to place cookies on our Website to deliver personalized advertisements and analyze the effectiveness of advertising campaigns. These third-party cookies are subject to the respective privacy policies of those third parties.</p>

<h2>Updates to this Policy</h2>

<p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology, legal requirements, or our practices. We encourage you to review this Policy periodically to stay informed about our use of cookies.</p>

<h2>Contact Us</h2>

<p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Cookie Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:[email address]">[email address]</a>.</p>